<section class="home-hero" aria-label="Registry Stack overview">
  <div class="home-hero-copy">
    <p class="home-kicker">For registry owners, integrators, and data protection reviewers</p>
    <h1 class="home-lede">
      Use the registries you already have, without exposing more data than needed.
    </h1>
    <p class="home-summary">
      Registry Stack puts a governed registry-facing layer in front of spreadsheets, extracts,
      databases, and legacy systems: metadata people can inspect, read-only APIs callers can use,
      evidence responses that avoid default full-record sharing, and audit trails reviewers can
      follow.
    </p>
    <p class="home-fit-line">
      Not a workflow engine, exchange layer, wallet, or replacement registry. Registry Stack makes
      existing registry data serviceable, inspectable, and safer to use.
    </p>
    <div class="home-actions" aria-label="Primary paths">
      <a class="home-action home-action-primary" href="./use-cases/legacy-registry-api/">Expose existing data</a>
      <a class="home-action" href="./capabilities/">See capabilities</a>
      <a class="home-action" href="./start/quickstart/">Choose where to start</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="home-signal-panel" aria-label="Registry Stack sequence">
    <div class="home-step">
      <span class="home-step-index">01</span>
      <strong>Describe what exists</strong>
      <span>Publish registry metadata, schemas, policies, services, and evidence offerings.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="home-step">
      <span class="home-step-index">02</span>
      <strong>Expose only what is allowed</strong>
      <span>Serve protected, read-only, entity-shaped APIs over sources already in use.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="home-step">
      <span class="home-step-index">03</span>
      <strong>Return evidence, not records</strong>
      <span>Answer with a configured status, predicate, selected value, or supported credential.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="home-band" aria-labelledby="home-problem-title">
  <div>
    <p class="home-section-label">The problem</p>
    <h2 id="home-problem-title">Data exists. The service contract around it often does not.</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="home-problem-grid">
    <a href="./problems/existing-data-not-service-ready/">
      <span>No safe service surface</span>
      Data exists in files, extracts, databases, or legacy systems, but other services cannot
      depend on a clear, approved interface.
    </a>
    <a href="./problems/registry-capabilities-hard-to-discover/">
      <span>No inspectable meaning</span>
      Integrators cannot see fields, schemas, policies, evidence offerings, or confidence
      boundaries before writing code.
    </a>
    <a href="./problems/apis-over-share-records/">
      <span>Too much disclosure</span>
      Callers need a status or evidence response, but broad record APIs move more data than the
      purpose requires.
    </a>
    <a href="./problems/ai-and-automation-increase-urgency/">
      <span>Unsafe connections get cheaper</span>
      AI-assisted clients and workflow tools can connect faster than purpose, meaning, disclosure,
      and audit can be reviewed.
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="home-band home-sequence-band" aria-labelledby="home-sequence-title">
  <div>
    <p class="home-section-label">The operating model</p>
    <h2 id="home-sequence-title">Start with the registry surface, then govern what crosses it.</h2>
  </div>
  <ol class="home-sequence">
    <li>
      <span>Make existing registries usable</span>
      <p>
        Registry Relay exposes protected, read-only, entity-shaped routes without moving source
        ownership into a new central system.
      </p>
      <a href="./capabilities/expose-protected-apis/">Expose protected APIs</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span>Make meaning inspectable</span>
      <p>
        Registry metadata describes fields, schemas, policies, services, and evidence offerings so
        people and tools can review the contract before integration.
      </p>
      <a href="./capabilities/describe-registries/">Describe registries</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <span>Return the evidence needed</span>
      <p>
        Registry Witness evaluates configured claims and returns the evidence shape the workflow
        needs: status, predicate, selected value, or supported credential.
      </p>
      <a href="./capabilities/certify-evidence/">Certify evidence</a>
    </li>
  </ol>
</section>

